                    <msContents>
                        <summary>45-47 are receipts from the payment of taxes for the annona militaris by Theodoros, son of Obodianos to the same persons. 45 and 46 were rolled together, and 47 was discovered within 20 cm of them. Payments are evidently not made to ofﬁcials, but rather to previous owners of the plots mentioned in each text. According to the general practice in Petra, although land had changed ownership, the tax registers were for some reason not updated for several years and the previous owner remained responsible for the tax payments. In 46 the ﬁrst signature can be ascribed to Patrikios, while the third one may belong to either Ailianos or Nikias. The second signature appears not to belong to any of the three men. </summary>
                        <msItemStruct>
                            <note type="general">Written transversa charta. Two margins are extant: top margin at least 6 cm and bottom margin at least 2.5 cm. The document was wrapped around the preceding one (45) and thus shares its physical characteristics, except that, being on the outer side, it is much less well preserved.</note>
                            <note type="general">Reproduced in plates LXVII–LXVIII</note>
                            <note type="local_note">Field no. XXXb</note>
